list.name: Default
list.comment:
Fixed ReflectedMembers, because FunctionSignatures were clashing due to synthetic members with identical signatures. Now, all synthetic members are filtered out, except for in rawMembers.
Null-annotated Retrier.

task.summary: got Hello World example to work in Spring Boot
added protobuf files for MTA GTFS Realtime API
got MTA GTFS realtime API to work using protobufs ported some unsafe, reflection, IO, and web stuff from old repo and improved a bunch of it, too

cleaned up protobuf code, including refactoring String <=> ByteString conversions
added a simple FeedController that just prints a Feed to JS in HTML so that I can inspect it using Chrome's better object inspector

wrote a more robust Retrier using MappedList
MappedList wraps a delegate list and using a mapping function, presents a lazily mapped view of delegated list. MappedSpliterator is similar, and both inherit from Mapper, which just contains a few convenience methods (maybe it should be an interface with default methods).
Retrier<T, R> uses a BiConsumer<List<T>, List<R>> to repeatedly try a List<T>, whose errors go into a List<R>. A reconverter Function<R, T> then maps the errors back for Retrier to try again.
Retrier supports an optimized version where the reconverter is the identity, that is T = R.
Exceptional Retriers can also be used that map a List<T> to a List<Pair<T, Exception>>, where Exception can be any exception type, with Exception, RuntimeException, and IOException built in (accessible through Retrier.builders()).
made a few changes to Mapper, MappedList, and MappedSpliterator, incl. documentation

fixed some reflector stuff (incl. always running setAccessible through a method handle (to avoid security checks)
added some more util classes
worked on ProtoFileFormatter, which help format generated Java proto files
worked on ProtoFileFormatter, about to convert to IntelliJ plugin module
refactored Reflectors package and added immutable package for ImmutableCollections, (only ImmutableArrayList implemented now)
added clearing mechanism to ReflectedMembers so that they can be un-cached more efficiently

finished ProtoFileFormatter#replaceDeprecatedValueOfWithForNumber
added Imports class extending Classes (with a BiMap b/w Class and simpleName)
added type parameter to ReflectedConstructor, ReflectedConstructors, and ReflectedClass

didn't finish ProtoFileFormatter::refactorStringAndByteStringGetters finished all the finding the correct methods and fields through reflection, but not making the actual code changes
made a bunch of other small changes to many classes, incl. formatting
moved collection classes in util to util.collections

fixed Reflected classes so that ReflectedMembers are indexed by their Signature, which is String for ReflectedFields and FunctionSignatures for ReflectedFunctions (ReflectedMethods and ReflectedConstructors)

added better methods to ReflectedClass for methods and constructors, and switched FunctionSignature to using factory methods: ofFunction, forMethod, and forConstructor, where the forConstructor uses a null function name (since it will only be compared to other constructors)

added ChainReference, which holds a chain of reference counts such that increasing a child's count increase it's parents, but not vice versa
used ChainReference in revised Reflector so that spawnChild() returns a new Reflector with chain()ed ChainReferences, so that when spawnChild().clear() is called, the actual ReflectedClasses are only removed from the cache if all references to it are gone
Note: all the ChainedReference stuff is all untested
